(1, 1, 'From Struggle Comes Success', 'http://www.mairovergara.com/from-struggle-comes-success/', 'https://youtu.be/ObD0F0vJSJA', 'From Struggle Comes Success\r\n\r\n1 â€“ [Escrita do comeÃ§o do vÃ­deo] Five years ago, Josef Azam was loading luggage at an airport. Today, he is the CEO of a multi-million dollar marketing and design agency. To date, Josef has generated over 250 million dollars in sales for his clients.\r\n\r\n2 â€“ [ComeÃ§o da fala] Everybody sees me today in the position Iâ€™m in, a fast growing company. They donâ€™t really understand the story and the struggle behind my success; where Iâ€™ve come from, and really what it takes to achieve success.\r\n\r\n3 â€“ My story starts like many others around this world; it starts unfortunately growing up in poor situation. I grew up in a pretty wealthy area being poor, and I think thereâ€™s nothing worse in life, than growing up poor in the face of people having everything.\r\n\r\n4 â€“ It makes you really realize what you donâ€™t have. When you grow up in an area where nobody has anything, youâ€™re kind of all on a level playing field. But when you grow up in a wealthy area, where everybody seems to have so much more than you, you know, you know that you donâ€™t have as much as them. You know your parents donâ€™t have as much money. I realize what I donâ€™t have, I realize what I wanted, and I made sure from a very young age, that I would succeed at every goal Iâ€™ve ever dreamt of.\r\n\r\n5 â€“ Seeing my parents work and struggle inspired me to work. I didnâ€™t have the money, like everybody else did when they went to University where their parents paid for them, and they had the nice cars, I worked three jobs to put myself through University. I graduated, and till this day Iâ€™m so thankful that I had to go through those experiences, because itâ€™s those struggles and those hardships that define me as a person.\r\n\r\n6 â€“ You need to sacrifice almost everything to achieve your goal. So when people say â€