(8, 7, 'Habit 1 Of Highly Effective People - Be Proactive', 'http://www.mairovergara.com/aprendendo-ingles-com-videos-007-habit-1-of-highly-effective-people-be-proactive/', 'https://youtu.be/vyaG64--Bpc', 'Habit 1 Of Highly Effective People - Be Proactive\r\n\r\nHi there,\r\n\r\nSteve Kaufmann. This is going to be the first in a series of 7 videos where I deal with each of the seven habits of highly effective people that Stephen Covey covers in his book, which I made a reference to in my video last week. First of all Iâ€™ll go over very quickly the 7 habits and this is advice for people in their lives, advice for Managers, advice for business people and for people generally. The Stephen Covey, and you can Google Stephen Covey, C.O.V.E.Y, 7 habits and you will get a lot more information, but there are 7 habits.\r\n\r\nThe first 3 have to do with Independence. The second 3 have to do with interdependence and the 7th one has to do with constantly renewing yourself and constantly improving.\r\n\r\nSo the first one today, I am going to talk about, is the need to be proactive. I think itâ€™s true in many things in life, if we wait for things to happen to us, some things may have, I mean, many things will happen to you. However by being proactive, by taking initiatives, by pursuing your goals, it is more likely that good things are going to happen to you. And certainly I found in language learning that as long as I was a passive learner in school with a Teacher teaching me and as long as I waited for the Teacher somehow or the text book to teach me, I wasnâ€™t making very good progress.\r\n\r\nOnce I took control of my learning, once I went out â€“ and this meant looking for things in the language that interested me; books, in the case of Chinese, books with, in those days before the internet, books with vocabulary lists behind each chapter. Taking the initiative in terms of what I wanted to learn about, what aspects of the language I needed to work on.\r\n\r\nTaking the initiative not to stay with the program that the Teacher is leading you into, in the classroom. Many Teachers donâ€™t like this. They donâ€™t want the students to get ahead of them, this is so wrong because the language isnâ€™t just chapter 1, chapter 2, and chapter 3. The language is basically a whole package and we learn different parts of it again and again and again and so for the student to go out and find things of interest to him or her and then go back and do what they are doing in class, all of this is good. You have to take the initiative, you have to take responsibility.\r\n\r\nThere are people who say that thereâ€™s no bad learners, thereâ€™s only a bad teacher. I donâ€™t believe that at all. I think whether you are in a classroom, or whether you are studying on your own, only those learners who take the initiative, who are motivated enough to take charge of their learning, are going to be successful. And we have ample evidence of this in our school system in Canada, and I am sure in other language schools where a small percentage of the learners actually improve and equally large numbers can improve on their own if they are motivated, so that the important point is not the number of instructional hours, the important point is; to what extend are you prepared to be proactive and take charge of your own learning.\r\n\r\nSo that is the first of the 7 habits that Stephen Covey talks about and it might even be the most important.\r\n\r\nBe proactive. Take charge of your own learning. And that is the first of the 7 habits of highly effective people.\r\n\r\nThank you for listening.\r\n\r\nBye for now.', 'HÃ¡bito 1 Das Pessoas Altamente Eficientes - Seja Proativo\r\n\r\nOlÃ¡,\r\n\r\nSteve Kauffmann. Esse vai ser o primeiro de uma sÃ©rie de 7 vÃ­deos onde eu lido com cada um dos sete hÃ¡bitos das pessoas altamente efetivas, que Stephen Covey aborda em seu livro, o qual eu fiz uma referÃªncia no meu vÃ­deo semana passada. Primeiro de tudo, eu vou abordar muito rapidamente os 7 hÃ¡bitos, isso serve como conselho de vida para as pessoas, conselho para administradores, conselho para pessoas de negÃ³cio e para pessoas em geral. O Stephen Coveyâ€¦vocÃª pode pesquisar no google por Stephen Covey  C.O.V.E.Y, 7 hÃ¡bitos, e vocÃª vai conseguir muito mais informaÃ§Ã£o, mas, existem 7 hÃ¡bitos.\r\n\r\nOs primeiros 3 tem a ver com independÃªncia. Os prÃ³ximos 3 tem a ver com interdependÃªncia e o sÃ©timo tem a ver com renovar-se constantemente e melhoramento constante.\r\n\r\nEntÃ£o o primeiro de hoje, eu vou falar sobre a necessidade de ser proativo. Eu penso que isso Ã© verdade em muitas coisas na vida, se nÃ³s esperÃ¡rmos que as coisas acontenÃ§am para nÃ³s, alguma coisas podem acontecer, quero dizer, muitas coisas vÃ£o acontecer para vocÃª. No entanto, sendo proativo e tomando iniciativas e perseguindo seus objetivos, Ã© mais provÃ¡vel que coisas boas vÃ£o acontecer com vocÃª. E certamente eu descobri no aprendizado de idiomas, que, enquanto eu era um aprendiz passivo na escola, com um professor me ensinando e enquanto eu esperava pelo professor ou pelo livro me ensinar de algum modo, eu nÃ£o estava fazendo um bom progresso.\r\n\r\nUma vez que eu tomei controle do meu aprendizado, uma vez que eu saÃ­ â€“ e isso significava procurar por coisas no idioma que me interessavam; livros, no caso do ChinÃªs, livros com,  naqueles dias, antes da internet, livros com listas de vocabulÃ¡rio atrÃ¡s de cada capÃ­tulo. Tomando a iniciativa em termos do que eu queria aprender a respeito, que aspectos da lÃ­ngua eu precisava trabalhar.\r\n\r\nTomar a iniciativa, nÃ£o ficar com o programa que o professor estÃ¡ guiando vocÃª dentro da sala de aula. Muitos professores nÃ£o gostam disso. Eles nÃ£o querem que os alunos passem na frente deles, isso Ã© muito errado porque o idioma nÃ£o Ã© sÃ³ capÃ­tulo 1, capÃ­tulo 2, capÃ­tulo 3. A lÃ­ngua Ã© basicamente um pacote inteiro e nÃ³s aprendemos partes diferentes disso de novo, de novo e de novo e entÃ£o para o aluno, sair e achar coisas de interesse para ele ou ela e depois voltar e fazer o que vocÃª estÃ¡ fazendo na classe, isso tudo Ã© bom. VocÃª tem que tomar a iniciativa, vocÃª tem que tomar responsabilidade.\r\n\r\nHÃ¡ pessoas que dizem que nÃ£o existem maus alunos, existe somente mau professor. Eu nÃ£o acredito nisso nem um pouco. Eu penso que se vocÃª estÃ¡ numa sala de aula, ou se vocÃª estÃ¡ estudando por conta prÃ³pria, somente aqueles alunos que tomarem a iniciativa, que estÃ£o motivados o suficiente para tomar conta do seu aprendizado, vÃ£o ter sucesso. E nÃ³s temos ampla evidÃªncia disso nas nossas escolas no Canada, e eu tenho certeza que em outras escolas de idiomas onde (somente) uma pequena porcentagem dos alunos melhoram de fato e igualmente um nÃºmero grande consegue melhorar por conta prÃ³pria se eles estiverem motivados. Assim o ponto importante nÃ£o Ã© o nÃºmero de horas de instruÃ§Ã£o, o ponto importante Ã©; atÃ© que ponto vocÃª estÃ¡ preparado para ser proativo e tomar conta do seu aprendizado.\r\n\r\nEntÃ£o esse Ã© o primeiro dos 7 hÃ¡bitos que Stephen Covey fala sobre e esse pode mesmo ser o mais importante.\r\nSeja proativo. Tome conta do seu prÃ³prio aprendizado. E esse Ã© o primeiro dos 7 hÃ¡bitos das pessoas altamente eficientes.\r\n\r\nObrigado por ouvir.\r\n\r\nAtÃ© mais, por agora.', '2017'),
(9, 8, 'The Ultimate Motivational Clip - Rise And Shine', 'http://www.mairovergara.com/aprendendo-ingles-com-videos-008-the-ultimate-motivational-clip-rise-shine/', 'https://youtu.be/hbkZrOU1Zag', 'The Ultimate Motivational Clip - Rise And Shine\r\n\r\nRise and shine.\r\n\r\nItâ€™s 6am and your hand canâ€™t make it to the alarm clock before the voices in your head start telling you that itâ€™s too early, too dark, and too cold to get out of a bed. Aching muscles lie still in rebellion, pretending not to hear your brain commanding them to move. A legion of voices are shouting their unanimous permission for you to hit the snooze button and go back to dreamland, but you didnâ€™t ask their opinion.\r\n\r\nThe voice youâ€™ve chosen to listen to is one of defiance. A voice that says there was a reason you set that alarm in the first place. So sit up, put your feet on the floor, and donâ€™t look back because weâ€™ve got work to do. Welcome to The Grind.\r\n\r\nFor what is each day but a series of conflicts between the right way and the easy way, 10,000 streams fan out like a river delta before you, Each one promising the path of least resistance. Thing is, youâ€™re headed upstream and when you make that choice, when you decide to turn your back on whatâ€™s comfortable and whatâ€™s safe and what some would call â€œcommon sense,â€ well thatâ€™s day one.\r\n\r\nFrom there it only gets tougher. So just make sure this is something you want. Because the easy way out will always be there, ready to wash you away, all you have to do is pick up your feet. But you arenâ€™t going to, are you? With each step comes the decision to take another Youâ€™re on your way now, but this is no time to dwell on how far youâ€™ve come. Youâ€™re in a fight against an opponent you canâ€™t see, but oh you can feel him on your heels canâ€™t you? Feel him breathing down your neck You know what that is? Thatâ€™s youâ€¦\r\n\r\nYour fears, your doubts and insecurities all lined up like a firing squad ready to shoot you out of the sky. But donâ€™t lose heart, while they arenâ€™t easily defeated, they are far from invincible. Remember this is The Grind, The Battle Royale between you and your mind, your body and the devil on your shoulder whoâ€™s telling you that this is just a game, this is just a waste of time, your opponents are stronger than you.\r\n\r\nDrown out the voice of uncertainty with the sound of your own heartbeat, burn away your self doubt with the fire thatâ€™s beneath you, remember what weâ€™re fighting for and never forget that momentum is a cruel mistress. She can turn on a dime with the smallest mistake. She is ever searching for that weak place in your armor. That one tiny thing you forgot to prepare for. So as long as the devil is hiding the details, the question remains, â€œIs that all you got?â€ â€œAre you sure?â€ And when the answer is â€œyes.â€ That youâ€™ve done all you can to prepare yourself for battle\r\n\r\nThen itâ€™s time to go forth and boldly face your enemy, the enemy within only now you must take that fight into the open, into hostile territory. Youâ€™re a lion in a field of lions, all hunting the same elusive prey with a desperate starvation that says:Victory is the only thing that can keep you alive.\r\n\r\nSo believe that voice that says â€œyou can run a little fasterâ€ and that â€œyou can throw a little harderâ€ and that, for you, the laws of physics are merely a suggestion.\r\n\r\nLuck is the last dying wish of those who want to believe that winning can happen by accident. Sweat on the other hand is for those who know itâ€™s a choice. So decide now because destiny waits for no man.\r\n\r\nAnd when your time comes and a thousand different voices are trying to tell you that youâ€™re not ready for it, listen instead to that lone voice of descent, that one voice that says: â€œyou are readyâ€ â€œyou are prepared.â€ Itâ€™s all up to you now!â€\r\n\r\nSo Rise and Shine.', 'O Clipe Motivacional Definitivo - Acorde E Brilhe\r\n\r